Hello Claude271,
To have gone through the state you describe (after a series of mix-ups, chatterboxes, micropoints, taz, finally everything that passed by there),
If I can give you advice, it's simply to tell you that all this is just psychological.
In general, the more you worry about these states, the worse they will get.
A very simple thing in such cases, you take deep breaths, breathe softly, and lie down in a place where you feel safe, and not too close to the walls (yes sometimes you can have the impression that they are closing in on you).
At the end of several months after a seizure, especially when you mix substances, you can find effects, especially after a sudden stop of the substances.
Don't worry, it's just a matter of time.
But as Claude532 said, consulting a psychiatrist can also help you get rid of the voices that are crowding your head.
Keep the fish, and stay positive.
